/gene_symbol.tsv` (gene_id \u2192 symbol). For each\npeak, join GeneID via V22=tx and GeneSymbol via the gene_id, and save a TSV\nto `output/annotated.bed` with columns\n`Chromosome, Start, End, Width, Strand, Score, nWindows, logFC.up, logFC.down,\nPValue, FDR, direction, rep.test, rep.logFC, best.logFC, best.test, best.start,\nName, GeneStrand, Distance, GeneID, GeneSymbol` (write.table tab-sep, no row\nnames, no quotes).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/annotated.bed` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: annotated.bed under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"gene_symbol.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"gene_symbol.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"peaks_with_nearest.bed\": {\n      \"_file\": \"peaks_with_nearest.bed\"\n    },\n    \"t2g.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"t2g.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/annotated.bed` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_TjPebLtC7y4SG4mM8McHc3lc", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files: `peaks_with_nearest.bed`, `t2g.tsv`, and `gene_symbol.tsv` using R.\\n2. Use the `dplyr` package to join the data:\\n   - First, join `peaks_with_nearest.bed` with `t2g.tsv` using column V22 from `peaks_with_nearest.bed` and the first column from `t2g.tsv` to get the GeneID.\\n   - Then, join the result with `gene_symbol.tsv` using the GeneID and the first column from `gene_symbol.tsv` to get the GeneSymbol.\\n3. Select and rename the columns as specified in the task.\\n4. Write the final annotated data to `output/annotated.bed` as a tab-separated f